{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6f621270-8ffc-4eeb-8f52-e274cabb01bc","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. **Update packages** — replace `xunit.runner.visualstudio` with `xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"2.9.3\" />\n```\n\n2. **Enable the new platform** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n3. **Run tests** with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nOr run the test project directly as an executable (Microsoft.Testing.Platform builds your test project as a standalone app).\n\n**Optional but recommended:**\n- Add `<GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>` (default is `true`) if you want the entry point auto-generated.\n- Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` if present — it's no longer needed, though it won't break anything if left in.\n\nThat's it — no code changes to your tests are required.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"37632f8f-a24a-492f-9672-4640f42ab516","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":374,"requestId":"BC52:1CADF2:1B5F3F8:1E6E8AB:69FA8FE9"},"id":"87d6f077-ad05-4273-98d9-5293fbd7d5da","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:48:50.586Z","parentId":"c1aa1dc8-c339-44fe-8c7c-93a19f500cf4"}
